        "subtitle": "Flagship ZDP189 — The Sharpest Edge in the Range",
        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>Xinzuo X05Z Zhen Series</strong> is the flagship of the entire Xinzuo range. At its core is Japanese <strong>ZDP189 powder steel</strong> from Hitachi — one of the hardest knife steels commercially available, heat-treated to an extraordinary HRC 65–67. This extreme hardness delivers edge retention that outlasts virtually every other kitchen knife on the market. Handles are crafted from rare North American desert ironwood with white buffalo horn bolsters, creating a blade that is as collectible as it is functional. The trade-off for this performance is maintenance: ZDP189 requires skilled sharpening with fine-grit whetstones. The X05Z is built for knife enthusiasts and professionals who understand steel and want the absolute best edge money can buy.</p>",
