      "settings": {
        "heading": "Learn more about the X05Z Zhen Series",
        "content": "<p>Understand <strong>powder steel technology</strong> and how it enables the extreme hardness of the Zhen Series blade core. <a href=\"/blogs/news/powder-steel-knife-guide-14cr14movnb\">Powder steel guide</a></p><p>At HRC 65–67, the X05Z is the hardest knife in the Xinzuo range. Learn what <strong>extreme Rockwell hardness</strong> means for edge life and maintenance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-steel-hardness-guide\">Steel hardness guide</a></p><p>Sharpening ZDP189 requires precision. Our <strong>angle guide</strong> helps you maintain the correct bevel for optimal performance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-sharpening-angle-guide\">Sharpening angle guide</a></p><p>Step-by-step <strong>whetstone sharpening</strong> for high-hardness steel — essential reading for X05Z owners. <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-sharpen-knives-whetstone\">How to sharpen on a whetstone</a></p><p>Want powder steel with easier maintenance? The <strong>Lan Series</strong> uses 14Cr14MoVNb at HRC 62 — still exceptional, but more forgiving to sharpen. <a href=\"/collections/lan-series\">Shop the Lan Series</a></p><p>Compare all series side by side. <a href=\"/blogs/news/xinzuo-knives-series-comparison-guide\">Full series comparison guide</a></p>",
